OL,3,CWoman, 84, 'terrified' as tax office
OL,4,Csends her #1,600 bill
OL,6,FWhen questioned about Ms Wall's
OL,7,Fspecific case, Mr Bloomfield says he
OL,8,Fcannot comment on individual matters
OL,9,Fbut that the fines would indicate she
OL,10,Fhas not filed a 2022 tax return by the
OL,11,Fdeadline of 29 February 2024.
OL,13,FHe says that reminders and follow-up
OL,14,Fletters are sent out to islanders and
OL,15,Fhe advises Ms Wall to submit a return
OL,16,Fnow, saying any potential revisions
OL,17,Fcan be made after the assessment.
